casebody.data:
Kwame ANANE
v.
WAKE COUNTY, North Carolina. No. 404P05. Supreme Court of North Carolina. August 3, 2005. Kwame Anane, Pro Se. William P. Hart, Special Deputy Attorney General, for State.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the application filed by Plaintiff on the 2nd day of August 2005 in this matter for Writ of Habeas Corpus, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court, Wake County:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 3rd day of August 2005."
